<p><strong>Prof Fang's Journal</strong></p>
<p><strong>Day 1</strong></p>
<p>Cups of tea: 0, Number of biscuits: 2</p>
<p>Had a lovely time counting the number of birds I saw in the garden, had a couple of biscuits</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Day 2</strong></p>
<p>Cups of tea: 2, Number of biscuits: 3.5</p>
<p>Accidentally dropped half a biscuit on the floor.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Day 3</strong></p>
<p>Cups of tea: 1, Number of biscuits: 3</p>
<p>Solved the problem I&rsquo;ve been working on! Had a celebratory cup of tea.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Day 4</strong></p>
<p>Cups of tea: 3, Number of biscuits: 5</p>
<p>Got stuck on a new problem, so 3 cups of tea.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Day 5</strong></p>
<p>Cups of tea: 5, Number of biscuits: 7.5</p>
<p>A tough day today, more tea and biscuits were needed. Split the last biscuit between me and a friend.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Day 6</strong></p>
<p>Cups of tea: 4, Number of biscuits: 6</p>
<p>Got stuck on a new problem, but made lots of good work today! And lots of tea.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Day 7</strong></p>
<p>Cups of tea: 1.9, Number of biscuits: 4</p>
<p>Watched more birds in the garden, forgot about one of my teas. Luckily I'd drunk most of it (90%).</p>
